column5: Hours
Is the motor housed correctly and free of damage?
Are all guards fuel levels acceptable?
Are all hoses fitted correctly and free from leaks? (Pump motors)
Test the Residual Current Device. Does it function as designed? (Electrical generators)
Does the motor start?
Is the data plate intact and legible?
Are hydraulics in good working order? (rams, pumps, hoses)
Are outriggers and their locking mechanism working properly?
Is the slew ring or articulation point free of damage?
Is the load cell, limiter and anti-two block working properly?
Are all welds, boom sections and other structural elements free of damage?
Are wire rope, sheaves, hook and wear pads in good working order?
Are all bolts, locking pins and guides in place?
Is the data plate intact and legible?
Are hydraulics in good working order? (rams, pumps, hoses)
Are all welds, booms sections and other structural elements free of damage?
Is the slew ring or articulation point free of damage?
Are the ground excavating tools in good working order? (Bucket, cutting edge, augers)
Are all bolts, locking pins and guides in place?
Are the ground conditions suitable?
column7: Do not continue if ground conditions are not suitable

column5: Are hydraulics in good working order? (rams, pumps, hoses)
Are the outriggers and their locking mechanism working properly?
Is the slew ring free of damage?
Are all welds, boom sections and other structural elements free of damage?
Are the attachment points, emergency descent device and handrails in place?
Have the secondary ground controls and communication methods been checked?
Is the load sensors and wind meter working properly?
Are all bolts, locking pins and guides in place?
